brand.name: Just Produce
metaData.Ingredients: Mix of Lettuces, Swiss Chard and Sorrel
metaData.Key Information: Not your typical salad mix. Tangy and Refreshing even without sauces! Tastes like a fresh squeeze of lemon straight from our sorrel leaves. Forget about adding sauces, Just Sorrel brightens any dish. Have it on its own as a salad, or pair it with fatty fishes like salmon. Grown and harvested locally, you get the maximum freshness that cannot be found in supermarkets. No pesticide nor GMO, you dont have to worry about harmful chemicals when enjoying Just Produce.

metaData.Key Information: The Australian carrots are extremely crunchy.
metaData.Preparation:
1. Peel and slice the carrots
2. Fill pan with 3cm of salt water and boil it
3. Add the carrot slices and continue boiling before reducing the heat and covering the pan
4. Cook until the carrots are tender but not soft
5. This will take about 10 – 15 minutes

brand.name: Just Produce
metaData.Ingredients: Mix of Lettuces, Swiss Chard and Mustard
metaData.Key Information: Not your typical salad mix. Intense with wasabi rush! Crispy with an intense wasabi-like flavour, every bite packs a delicious punch. No need to add sauces, Zesty Mustard tastes great on its own. Best paired with meat and eggs, the wasabi-flavour is a unique addition that elevates your typical salad dish and gives it a spicy kick. Grown and harvested locally, you get the maximum freshness that cant be found in supermarkets. No pesticide nor GMO, you dont have to worry about harmful chemicals when enjoying Just Produce.

metaData.Key Information:
Red onion is purplish-red on its skins with white flesh tinged with red. It adds a distinct flavour to many dishes. They are often consumed raw, grilled, lightly saut»ed with other foods, or added as a decoration to salads. It tends to lose its colours when cooked.

Freshness Guarantee for Online Orders:
• We pick the freshest item(s) and deliver to your doorstep
• Opt for a refund within 3 days of delivery if your items are not delivered fresh
• Check out our refund policy for fresh in the T&C for more details
metaData.Preparation:
Ways to enjoy:
• Sliced: As tasty toppings for your hamburger
• Chopped: Tasty raw ingredients in salsa or stuffing
• Cooked: Healthy vegetable side dish
metaData.Storage Information:
• Best consumed within 14 days of delivery• Best stored in a cool, dry, dark and well-ventilated place
• Store it in an open basket, bamboo steamer, mesh bag or netted bag
• Avoid leaving onions in plastic bags as it will rot due to poor ventilation
• Avoid storing in refrigerator as it will turn mushy and rot due to moisture within the space
• Absorb moisture easily, hence if temperature or humidity is too high, it may start to sprout or rot

brand.name: Chef
metaData.Key Information:
• Yellow onion is a general cooking onion used in stews to sauté
• Typically when a cooked recipe calls for onion, yellow onion is a safe way to go
• Yellow onions have a yellow-brown papery skin on the outside and a white flesh
• The flavour is strong with a hint of sweetness in them. This is also the onion used in burgers as caramelized onions.

metaData.Preparation:
Directions:
• Cut the top, then slice in half
• Using a sharp chef's knife, slice about a half an inch off the top of the onion and discard
• Peel off the papery layers
• Remove and discard the skin
• Chop vertically
• Take one onion half and lay it flat on your cutting board
• Chop horizontally
metaData.Storage Information:
• Best consumed within 14 days of delivery• Best stored in a cool, dry, dark and well-ventilated place
• Store it in an open basket, bamboo steamer, mesh bag or netted bag
• Avoid leaving onions in plastic bags as it will rot due to poor ventilation
• Avoid storing in refrigerator as it will turn mushy and rot due to moisture within the space
• Absorb moisture easily, hence if temperature or humidity is too high, it may start to sprout or rot

metaData.Key Information:
Broccoli belongs to the cabbage family; it is made up of edible large flowering head and stalk. It comes in a variety of colours ranging from dark sage to dark and purplish green. It is power packed with vitamins and nutrients, suitable for the young and old.
Freshness Guarantee for Online Orders:
• We pick the freshest item(s) and deliver to your doorstep
• Opt for a refund within 3 days of delivery if your items are not delivered fresh
• Check out our refund policy for fresh in the T&C for more details
metaData.Preparation:
Ways to enjoy:
• Steamed: Put it in the microwave and serve with a little salt, vinegar and olive oil
• Roasted: Bake the broccoli with plenty of olive oil, salt and pepper (seasonings) at 400 degrees F in the oven for 15 minutes until it becomes crisp tender or begins to turn brown. Flip the broccoli halfway while cooking to ensure it is cooked evenly. Serve with freshly grated Parmesan cheese on top.
• Serve with pasta: Incorporate it into your paste as one of the ingredients
metaData.Storage Information:
• To maintain its optimum quality for longer, store the item(s) whole in the fridge
• Best consumed within 7 days of delivery
• Rinse the broccoli head and wrap loosely in a damp towel
• Keep it refrigerated and consume within 2 to 3 days
• Avoid storing broccoli in a sealed container or plastic bag as raw broccoli requires air circulationAnother storage method:
• Submerge stem in wide mouthed jug containing iced water
• Cover the broccoli head loosely with a plastic bag
• Change ice water dailyThis method helps to keep your broccoli fresh and crisp for the whole week.Freezing:• Cut washed broccoli and steam/blanch them for about 5 minutes
• Plunge them into iced water to stop cooking
• Drain thoroughly
• Place them in a sealed bag or container
• Freeze up to 12 months
